        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2544210093" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5527627067725259460">There is a murder. There is a suspect. There is a policeman. Yet in the brief space of a few fairly straight-forward chapters, these elements transform. The crime becomes a chessboard. The perpetrator turns to pieces of black, the lawman to pieces of white, as we pull back to meet the true players - two academics, friends from long ago, who find themselves facing off in a battle of wits.<br/><br/>Everything here is deceptive, including the modest reserve with which Higashino relays his tale. Those sleeves</span>
  <span id="freeText5527627067725259460" style="display:none">There is a murder. There is a suspect. There is a policeman. Yet in the brief space of a few fairly straight-forward chapters, these elements transform. The crime becomes a chessboard. The perpetrator turns to pieces of black, the lawman to pieces of white, as we pull back to meet the true players - two academics, friends from long ago, who find themselves facing off in a battle of wits.<br /><br />Everything here is deceptive, including the modest reserve with which Higashino relays his tale. Those sleeves of his are filled with tricks...and a single hidden heart.<br /></span>
